BULLETIN - EAS ACTIVATION REQUESTED
CHILD ABDUCTION EMERGENCY
TEXAS DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC SAFETY
Relayed by National Weather Service Houston/Galveston TX
627 AM CDT Sat Sep 25 2021

...AMBER ALERT...

THE FOLLOWING MESSAGE IS TRANSMITTED AT THE REQUEST OF THE TEXAS
DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC SAFETY.

THE FOLLOWING MESSAGE IS TRANSMITTED AT THE REQUEST OF THE TEXAS
DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC SAFETY.

THIS IS A CHILD ABDUCTION ALERT ISSUED BY THE TEXAS AMBER ALERT
NETWORK

THE BOSQUE COUNTY SHERIFFS OFFICE IS SEARCHING FOR JESSI MARIE
LOWREY, WHITE, FEMALE, 7 YEARS OLD, 3 FOOT ZERO INCHES TALL, 40
POUNDS, BROWN HAIR DYED BLUE, BROWN EYES, WEARING A BLUE BOW, BLUE
T-SHIRT WITH STARS, AND BLACK PANTS WITH STARS.

POLICE ARE LOOKING FOR RANDALL ANTHONY THURMAN, WHITE, MALE, 34 YEARS
OLD, DATE OF BIRTH SEPTEMBER 11TH, 1987, 5 FEET 10 INCHES TALL, 185
POUNDS, BLONDE HAIR, HAZEL EYES, LAST SEEN WEARING A DARK SHIRT WITH
BLUE JEANS, IN CONNECTION WITH HER ABDUCTION.

THE SUSPECT IS DRIVING A SILVER, 2011, CHRYSLER 200 WITH A TEXAS
LICENSE PLATE NUMBER OF P D J 3 6 5 8.

THE SUSPECT WAS LAST HEARD FROM IN WALNUT SPRINGS, TEXAS.

LAW ENFORCEMENT OFFICIALS BELIEVE THIS CHILD TO BE IN GRAVE OR
IMMEDIATE DANGER.

IF YOU HAVE ANY INFORMATION REGARDING THIS ABDUCTION, CALL THE BOSQUE
COUNTY SHERIFFS OFFICE

NEWS MEDIA POINT OF CONTACT IS THE BOSQUE COUNTY SHERIFFS OFFICE AT 
2 5 4 4 3 5 2 3 6 3.


$$
